00:09:19.510 --> 00:09:23.040
So let me walk you through
cochlear implant 101

00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:27.830
so that you understand the kind
of technology that's in my head.

00:09:27.830 --> 00:09:31.620
So let's start by pretending
that this is a normal ear,

00:09:31.620 --> 00:09:34.110
without all this interesting
circuitry unit.

00:09:34.110 --> 00:09:39.710
In a normal ear, sound will
come in through the ear canal,

00:09:39.710 --> 00:09:43.910
hit the ear drum, which
makes these bones vibrate.

00:09:43.910 --> 00:09:47.060
That vibration is transmitted
through the cochlea,

00:09:47.060 --> 00:09:50.620
which is a hollowed tube filled
with liquid and tiny cells

00:09:50.620 --> 00:09:54.300
that resonate in response to sound.

00:09:54.300 --> 00:09:58.240
As those hear cells resonate,
these send sound signals

00:09:58.240 --> 00:10:01.640 position:56%
down the hearing nerve to the brain.

00:10:01.640 --> 00:10:04.700
The reason that most
people are deaf is

00:10:04.700 --> 00:10:09.530
that they lose those tiny
hair cells inside the cochlea.

00:10:09.530 --> 00:10:12.830
It's like stripping the
keys off of a piano.

00:10:12.830 --> 00:10:14.650
The strings are still there.

00:10:14.650 --> 00:10:18.720
The piano can still create sound,
except that there's no keys

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:21.490
to trigger those strings.

00:10:21.490 --> 00:10:27.030
Similarly, in my case, the
auditory nerve is intact,

00:10:27.030 --> 00:10:30.890
it's just that there are no tiny
hairs left inside my cochlea

00:10:30.890 --> 00:10:36.410
to vibrate in response to
sound, that's why I'm deaf.

00:10:36.410 --> 00:10:41.690
So what a cochlear implant does is
it replaces that mechanical system

00:10:41.690 --> 00:10:43.720
with an electronic system.

00:10:43.720 --> 00:10:47.160
So let me walk you
through how that works.

00:10:47.160 --> 00:10:49.140
Let's start with the outside.

00:10:49.140 --> 00:10:52.540
So on the outside you can see
this thing called a "headpiece".

00:10:52.540 --> 00:10:57.420
Now, that corresponds to this disc

00:10:57.420 --> 00:11:01.060
that you see here,
specifically this thing.

00:11:01.060 --> 00:11:06.590
Now, that headpiece, as you can
see, it actually sticks to my head.

00:11:06.590 --> 00:11:09.670
Okay. Stupid implant
tricks [laughter].

00:11:09.670 --> 00:11:16.520
That's because there's a magnet in
the headpiece that makes it stick

00:11:16.520 --> 00:11:20.010
to a magnet inside
the implant itself,

00:11:20.010 --> 00:11:23.400
so that explains why the
headpiece sticks there.

00:11:23.400 --> 00:11:25.610
But, what is the headpiece?

00:11:25.610 --> 00:11:28.580
Well, the headpiece
is taking a radio --

00:11:28.580 --> 00:11:32.960
or rather it's taking an electronic
signal from the thing on my ear,

00:11:32.960 --> 00:11:35.330 position:56%
which is a string of ones and zeros.

00:11:35.330 --> 00:11:36.940
It's digitized sound.

00:11:36.940 --> 00:11:43.260
And it is sending that string of
ones and zeros through my skin

00:11:43.260 --> 00:11:49.080
to the implant which is embedded
in my skull underneath the skin.

00:11:49.080 --> 00:11:51.110
It's not inside my skull.

00:11:51.110 --> 00:11:53.400
It's a not a brain implant.

00:11:53.400 --> 00:11:55.090
It's on top of the skull,

00:11:55.090 --> 00:11:57.590
countersunk into the
surface of the skull.

00:11:57.590 --> 00:12:01.910
And I'll show you a wonderfully
gory picture of that in a moment.

00:12:01.910 --> 00:12:04.940
&gt;&gt; Thanks for the warning.

00:12:04.940 --> 00:12:06.850
