&gt;&gt; [Inaudible] excited because
for the first time there was a way

00:30:32.090 --> 00:30:36.320 position:56%
to access the brain [inaudible], and
the brain being such a vital organ,

00:30:36.320 --> 00:30:39.790
it's quite understandable
you want to leave it alone.

00:30:39.790 --> 00:30:41.840
So the technology is there.

00:30:41.840 --> 00:30:44.280
Now, the question will be,
[inaudible] you actually put

00:30:44.280 --> 00:30:48.860
in the nanowires exactly
at the place you want.

00:30:48.860 --> 00:30:51.560
The answer is no, you can't.

00:30:51.560 --> 00:30:57.050
But, nanowires are very small,
so [inaudible] is very small

00:30:57.050 --> 00:31:01.350
which is [inaudible] that's
about, you know, 100 times less

00:31:01.350 --> 00:31:03.940
than the thickness of your hair.

00:31:03.940 --> 00:31:07.050
How do you push the
electrode to the brain?

00:31:07.050 --> 00:31:11.810
So what you do is you actually send
a certain number [inaudible] bundle

00:31:11.810 --> 00:31:14.010
and then the bundle
would probably be --

00:31:14.010 --> 00:31:20.400
I mean, nanowires would be allowed
to float into the blood stream

00:31:20.400 --> 00:31:23.420
until they can go no further.

00:31:23.420 --> 00:31:25.960
At the moment we can wire a rat.

00:31:25.960 --> 00:31:29.430
We can [inaudible] the
electrodes in the spinal cord.

00:31:29.430 --> 00:31:32.160
We want to know if we do so,

00:31:32.160 --> 00:31:36.530
how long would the wires
continue to work properly.

00:31:36.530 --> 00:31:38.970
We're talking about five years

00:31:38.970 --> 00:31:43.680
where it's a very basic
research that needs to be done.

00:31:45.310 --> 00:31:48.760
&gt;&gt; Dr. Michael Chorost: So, that's
one idea that's being floated

00:31:48.760 --> 00:31:53.190
around of actually wiring up
the brain from the inside.

00:31:53.190 --> 00:31:57.800
I personally am not too optimistic
about that particular technology

00:31:57.800 --> 00:32:02.240
because the issues of tangling
and clotting seem to me just to be

00:32:02.240 --> 00:32:07.480
so formidable as to pretty much
rule this out as a possibility.

00:32:07.480 --> 00:32:09.080
But there are other possibilities

00:32:09.080 --> 00:32:11.860
which are actually quite
a bit further along.

